</h3><p class="sc-ZOtfp cLnRKw pf-23_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Accidental amputations are unfortunately not uncommon, especially in workplaces where heavy machinery and equipment are prevalent. According to the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), in the UK alone, there were over 7,500 reported major injuries involving amputations in the year 2020/21. Furthermore, studies have shown that prompt first aid intervention significantly improves outcomes for individuals who have experienced amputations.

